result.execSummary:
Zachary F Hayes was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Zachary F Hayes was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
[ma] Case called at 8:33 AM 
Defendant Zachary F Hayes not in court.  Attorney Krysta Parson in court for State of Wisconsin. 

The Court has learned that Mr. Hayes has been picked up by extraditing state. 
The Court takes no further action, case can be closed. 

recess: 8:35am
Status conference on November 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Commitment Warrant

ec/pc: DA, Def, JESO (10/5/22--ma)
Letter to Judge Dehring regarding Extradition Waiver form
cc: DA, Def, JCJ, Governor ae 10/4/22

[ae] case called 2:15 PM Defendant Zachary F Hayes in court, in custody. Public Service Special Prosecutor Melanie Flint appears for the State of Wisconsin. 

Mr. Hayes verifies name and date of birth
Right to Counsel reviewed [Defendant declined to be evaluated by SPD]

The Court finds Defendant competent to represent himself; further that waiver of counsel is being made freely, voluntarily, and intelligently.

The Court finds that the Defendant is the same as charged in the complaint. 
The Court finds that the Defendant is a fugitive of justice. 

The Defendant has signed Waiver of Extradition paperwork. Defendant verifies receipt of the Complaint.
The Court orders Defendant committed to Jefferson County Jail not to exceed 30 days to allow time for requesting State to be picked up on warrant. 
recess 2:22 pm. 

NEXT: Status Conference on 11/1/22 at 8:30 am
